    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in Salt. The TLS module within SaltStack Salt through 3002 creates certificates with weak file permissions. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to confidentiality.\n            STATEMENT: Red Hat Ceph Storage 2 shipped salt for the usage of Red Hat Storage Console 2(RHSCON-2), which required salt to administrate ceph nodes. RHSCON-2 has reached End Of Life, hence salt is no longer used and supported. Therefore, the salt package provided by Red Hat Ceph Storage 2 has been marked as 'will not fix'.",
